                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d368">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 184/239a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-11-15T23:00:00+00:00"
                            >November 15, 1919—11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5221. Most urgent for the Secretary of State from Polk. Disappointed about <hi
                        rend="italic">George Washington</hi>. Shall I arrange to close Mission and
                    send Commissioners and all personnel of Commission home on <hi rend="italic"
                        >America</hi> between 1st and 5th of December? As I understand <hi
                        rend="italic">America</hi> is not in very good condition I may return on
                    regular liner via England, sailing some time in the first ten days of December.
                    I would appreciate very much your instructions as to closing Mission, matter of
                    communications service and work to be turned over to Ambassador. Please see my
                    5133, November 12, 3 p.m.,<note n="7" xml:id="d368fn7">Not printed.</note> and
                    5187, November 14, 8 p.m. Polk.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi
                        rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
